August 2009 Geography Practice Paper - Primary 6 "Based on my experience and knowledge, the most significant event for Singapore in the past 100 years is the reunification." I quote the first sentence of my book review on page 5 of Primary 6 Social Studies textbook formerly published by Straits Times Press a few years back.At the end of primary school, there is a certain tendency for the students to leave secondary school behind and look forward to a no longer ardour for formal education. Books are boring and least of all the students want to pare their noses into a whole textbook of Geography at one go, by trying to make a summary on the content on the History section of the book. In chapters 8 and 10 of the textbook, students will need to write a book review of a book related to the previous chapters 7 and 9 that have been studied previously; in this case, the two chapters are of history.Whenever the children are looking for answering questions set by the teacher to qualify as work, they should not be merely
